        {
            "doi": "10.1093/bioinformatics/btn341",
            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "We describe a web server for the automatic prediction of immunoglobulin variable domains based on the canonical structure model. The server is user-friendly and flexible. It allows the user to select the templates for the frameworks and the loops using different strategies. The final output is a full-fledged 3D model of the variable domains of the target immunoglobulin. \u00a9 The Author 2008. Published by Oxford University Press. All rights reserved.",
